    <!-- KEY TOPICS TAB -->
    <div id="topics" class="tab-content">
        <div class="section">
            <h2>📖 Core Pharmacovigilance Topics Explained</h2>

            <h3>1. Pharmacovigilance Fundamentals</h3>
            <div class="key-topics">
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>📌 Definition & Scope</strong>
                    <p>Science of detecting, assessing, understanding, and preventing adverse drug effects. Post-marketing surveillance.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🎯 Objectives</strong>
                    <p>Improve drug safety, enhance efficacy-safety ratio, support regulatory decisions, protect public health.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🔄 Workflow</strong>
                    <p>Report collection → Assessment → Coding (MedDRA) → Database management → Signal detection → Action.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">2. Adverse Drug Reactions</h3>
            <div class="key-topics">
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🚨 Definition</strong>
                    <p>Any noxious, unintended response occurring at therapeutic doses. WHO and ICH definitions.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>📊 Classification</strong>
                    <p>Type A–E (WHO), Severity (Mild, Moderate, Severe), Outcome (Recovered, Recovering, Not recovered, Fatal, Unknown).</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🔬 Reporting</strong>
                    <p>Spontaneous reports, clinical trials, literature, regulatory databases. Mandatory vs. voluntary.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">3. Causality Assessment Methods</h3>
            <div class="key-topics">
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>📏 Naranjo Scale</strong>
                    <p>10-question algorithm; most common. Scores: Definite (≥9), Probable (5–8), Possible (1–4), Unlikely (≤0).</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🌍 WHO-UMC Scale</strong>
                    <p>6 categories: Certain, Probable/Likely, Possible, Unlikely, Unrelated, Unassessable. Narrative-based.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>⚙️ Factors in Assessment</strong>
                    <p>Temporal relationship, dose-response, dechallenge/rechallenge, alternative causes, previous reports.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">4. Regulatory Framework</h3>
            <div class="key-topics">
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🏛️ ICH Guidelines</strong>
                    <p>GCP (E6), Pharmacovigilance (E2A, E2B, E2C, E2D). International harmonization standards.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🇺🇸 FDA & USA</strong>
                    <p>FAERS database, 21 CFR Part 320, MedWatch, serious AERS reporting within 15 days.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🇮🇳 India (CDSCO)</strong>
                    <p>GVKS portal, PvPI program, PSUR/DSUR, Schedule Y compliance, 14–30 day reporting windows.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">5. Signal Detection & Data Analysis</h3>
            <div class="key-topics">
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>📡 Signal Definition</strong>
                    <p>Detected adverse event-drug association warranting further investigation. Based on disproportionality.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🔢 Statistical Methods</strong>
                    <p>ROR (Reporting Odds Ratio), PRR (Proportional Reporting Ratio), IC (Information Component), Chi-square test.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🗄️ Databases</strong>
                    <p>FAERS (FDA), EudraVigilance (EMA), VigiBase (WHO), GVKS (India). Public access with restrictions.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">6. Safety Documentation & Reporting</h3>
            <div class="key-topics">
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>📋 Case Report Form (CRF)</strong>
                    <p>Document for capturing ADR details. Includes demographics, drug info, ADR description, outcomes.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>📄 PSUR (Periodic Safety Update Report)</strong>
                    <p>Submitted annually/per schedule. Summarizes all safety data, signals, actions, and updates.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🔐 Medical Dictionary (MedDRA)</strong>
                    <p>Standardized adverse event coding. 5 levels: SOC, HLGT, HLT, PT, LLT. Essential for database harmonization.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">7. Risk Management & REMS</h3>
            <div class="key-topics">
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>⚖️ Risk-Benefit Assessment</strong>
                    <p>Evaluation of efficacy vs. safety. Considers populations, alternatives, therapeutic need.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🛡️ Risk Minimization</strong>
                    <p>Routine (labeling) or Additional (REMS, restricted distribution, monitoring). Proportionate to risk.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🚨 REMS Program</strong>
                    <p>Risk Evaluation Mitigation Strategy (US). Includes education, restricted dispensing, monitoring, enrollment.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">8. Special Populations & Topics</h3>
            <div class="key-topics">
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>👶 Pediatric Safety</strong>
                    <p>Off-label use, formulation issues, dosing challenges, special PV considerations.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🤰 Pregnancy & Lactation</strong>
                    <p>Teratogenicity, developmental toxicity, lactation effects. Category A–X drugs (FDA).</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>👴 Geriatric Pharmacology</strong>
                    <p>Age-related PK/PD changes, polypharmacy, higher ADR risk, dosing adjustments.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3 style="margin-top: 30px;">9. Emerging Topics</h3>
            <div class="key-topics">
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🤖 AI & Machine Learning</strong>
                    <p>Automated signal detection, predictive modeling, pattern recognition in large datasets.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>💊 Real-World Evidence (RWE)</strong>
                    <p>Safety data from electronic health records (EHRs), registries, observational studies.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="topic-card">
                    <strong>🔗 Blockchain & Traceability</strong>
                    <p>Counterfeit drug detection, supply chain transparency, distributed PV networks.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </div>

